article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 74, Cent. Michigan 71
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Paige Paulsen scored 22 points to lead Wisconsin-Milwaukee to a 74-71 victory over Central Michigan Wednesday night that snapped a six-game Panther losing streak. The Panthers (4-7) had only 10 scholarship players because leading scorer Torre Johnson, 17.8 points a game, was dismissed from the team this week after being charged with substantial battery for striking a woman and reserve guard Roman Gentry left for personal reasons. Deion James added 12 points and Marcus Skinner 10 for the Panthers. The Chippewas (4-6), who upset Michigan earlier this season 78-67, ended their four-game winning streak despite 25 points from Giordan Watson. The Chippewas beat Milwaukee 76-61 last season. Paulsen hit a 3-pointer to open scoring in the second half and increase the Panthers' lead to 40-31, and Milwaukee was ahead 62-55 after a 3-pointer by James with 6:29 left. The Chippewas came roaring back and pulled within a point at 69-68 on a pair of free throws by Watson with 37.1 seconds left. But Allan Hanson made a pair of free throws with 36 seconds remaining and James made one of two with 21.7 seconds left to increase the lead to 72-68 and put the game out of reach. Milwaukee led 37-31 after the first period. Skinner scored his team's first seven points as Milwaukee rolled to a 9-4 advantage. The Chippewas came back to tie the game at 11-11 on a dunk by Marcus Van but Paulsen responded with a 3-pointer and the Panthers stayed ahead the rest of the first period.
